To convert an input GDL file to the ground format used by the
UAMBAT project, use the following command:

./ground-gdl.sh <input lifted file> <output ground file>

--------------------

To setup the project, follow the following steps:

1. Install the 'opam' package

2. Initialize with the following:
opam init

3. Install the neccessary packages:
opam install ocamlfind
opam install menhir

4. Clone the GaDeLaC repository:
git clone git@bitbucket.org:Abdallah/gadelac.git

5. Make the GaDeLaC project:
cd gadelac
make

